We encourage you to apply regardless of your location. Your mission will be to help the Gamium team tech area by joining our technical area as Senior React Native Developer.  As a key member of the engineering team, you would be expected to come with good experience and knowledge from previous unity developing roles. With the support of more senior members of the company you would be expected to further develop your skills and knowledge, while at the same time helping to mentor then members of the team. While we are not expecting you to come in with full architecture plans, your ideas will be listened to from day one. Gamium is building the first decentralized social metaverse and the digital identity of humans. Create your avatar, exchange NFTs, get a job, socialize and earn in the Gamium world. It’s a 3D virtual environment where you can get immersive experiences built with Unity and where social interaction is rewarded, encouraging monetization models such as Socialize to Earn, using Blockchain technology. Are you passionate about challenges and delving into the most cutting-edge trends in blockchain, crypto, metaverse and the most Techie positions? Are you looking to boost your growth by the hands of the creators of the future? Then… GAMIUM is your next challenge! Our mision is to create the first metaverse that interconnects all of them, making avatars and assets multi-metaverse compatible. Create your avatar, exchange NFTs, get a job, socialize and earn in the Gamium world using blockchain technology and token standards. What will your contribution be?   Gamium is looking for an Senior React Native developer to join our mobile development team who will work closely with Design to transform UI specifications into beautiful, smooth, performant and near pixel perfect interactive interfaces. The ideal person will be comfortable working on features end-to-end, has an eye for design and visual detail, enjoys working with designers as well as developers, and who can transform reused UI patterns such as list items into reusable UI components.   The ideal candidate will love finessing UI implementations to the highest levels of quality and will care deeply about things like code cleanliness, reusability, maintainability, performance, and UI layout accuracy - as well as doing whatever needed to create a best-in-class user experience for Gamium’s users.   Your impact:   - Develop new features on a web3 based platform and enhance existing ones - Be one of our gurus on React Native and other mobile UI based technologies - Collaborate with colleagues in a fast-paced environment - Participate in software design   Desired Qualifications:   - 4+ years of experience implementing first class mobile user interfaces. - Experience with native Android UI development. - Experience with native iOS UI development. - Strong experience with CSS (including Bootstrap, SCSS, and other structured UI libraries) - Some experience with any of the following programming languages: Go, C#, Kotlin, Swift, Python. - Exposure to designing structured UI components and libraries. - Experience consuming both REST API and WS servicers for real-time applications   Requirements:   - Excitement for blockchain, Web 3.0, and similar decentralized technologies. - Willingness to both learn and share your knowledge with others. - Capability to work remotely in a distributed team. - Ability to work under pressure, we’re a fast paced startup, you’ll be working on many different things day to day. - A strong desire to grow and challenge yourself. While this role is mainly focused on maintenance, we would expect you to constantly find ways to improve and automate services under your purview. - Strong communication skills. You can give and receive constructive feedback, and you do not shy away from planning meetings and code reviews. You will be part of an extremely motivated team and should team together or team apart as needed.   What’s in it for you?   - High Standards: We accept the challenge of learning day by day, improving in our roles and how to add value to the future! We enjoy working driven by motivation for the project, teamwork and constant development. - ColleaguesTeam: We are a young and dynamic community that enjoys co-creating and developing the technology of the future, a team where we can all contribute and are supported by the best professionals full of talent, enthusiasm and vision facing new challenges. Inside Gamium, fun, collaboration, a good atmosphere and professionalism runs together. - Growth and Development: We want the person who joins our team to know the internal processes and the business, and to be able to grow and develop with us, working in a environment in which talent is breathed in every corner inside Gamium. The motivation for the Project, the energy and the desire to learn are keys to being part of Gamium’s team. - Self-organization: We believe in Independence to carry out our tasks. We pursue our goals and insist on giving the best version of ourselves while build the future inside Gamium. - Flexibility: At Gamium we care about the well-being of our contributors and therefore we know how to combine our work with personal life to be more effective, we are flexible because we all have a common goal and we are committed to the project. - Fully Remote: This role is location agnostic anywhere in the world. Though we ask that you overlap some working hours within GMT+1 Time Zone. We are a fully distributed team and have the tools and benefits to support you in your remote work environment. - Competitive salary: We offer you a fixed and variable salary in Tokens (valuable according to profile and experience) Gamium is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Immutable X is the first and leading Layer 2 scaling solution for NFTs on Ethereum, with zero gas fees &amp; is 100% carbon neutral. You will also be contributing to Immutable X’s commercial and product strategies, through iterating on the Partner Success technical consulting offerings, bringing feedback from our partners to internal stakeholders, and seeking opportunities to improve operational efficiency across the Partner Success organisation. You will have the opportunity to work on many initiatives and projects that extend beyond the commercial teams within the business. So come and join us if you’re ready to take on a new exciting challenge and be at the forefront of cutting edge technology!
